On February 18, 2022, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. declared that the national emergency concerning the COVID-19 pandemic, which was initially declared on March 13, 2020, will continue beyond March 1, 2022. This decision is based on the significant risk the pandemic continues to pose to the public health and safety of the nation. The declaration is in accordance with the National Emergencies Act and will be published in the Federal Register and transmitted to Congress.